Many popular wikis (Wikipedia included) provide a simple feature for navigating to a random page. While it might seem trivial, this is a great way for new/reluctant users to discover the breadth and depth of the wiki content, and also for wiki admins to spot-check the quality of contributed content. 

I'm not particular about how the feature is implemented, perhaps as a dashboard or space-level feature enabled by configuration, or even as a simple macro.

It seems like this would be fairly straightforward to implement, so I'm not sure why it's been overlooked/avoided thus far. Let me know if you have any questions and thanks for a great product thus far!

